data.name: Const_Msg_SOS_Description_1
data.value: Make sure you are out of danger before you do anything else. Find a safe place away from the road and flow of traffic.

data.name: Const_Msg_SOS_Description_2
data.value: if anyone involved is badly injured, if you suspect the third party of driving dangerously or illegally or if the vehicles involved are blocking the road.

data.name: Const_Msg_SOS_Description_3
data.value: or witnesses involved along with their contact details. It’s also important to make a note of how many people were travelling in the other vehicles involved.

data.name: Const_Msg_SOS_Description_5
data.value: if the accident occurred during business hours. Ask for the person responsible for your fleet.

data.name: Const_Msg_SOS_Description_6
data.value: with the third party(ies) that were involved, if you can – ideally find out who they’re insured by and get their policy number if they have it.

data.name: Const_Msg_SOS_Description_7
data.value: of the accident using your mobile phone. Try to photograph any areas of damage to your vehicle as well as the third party vehicles involved and also the position of the vehicles at the time of impact. If possible, try to capture vehicle registration plates.
